## Verification

- [ ] `createService()` creates a container, starts it, performs health check, and returns `Service` with status `"running"`
- [ ] `createService()` stops the container and throws if health check fails
- [ ] `updateService()` starts a new container, health-checks it, stops the old container on success
- [ ] `updateService()` keeps the old container running if the new container fails health check
- [ ] `deleteService()` stops and removes the container
- [ ] `deleteService()` handles non-existent containers gracefully
- [ ] `getServiceStatus()` returns `"running"` for a running container
- [ ] `getServiceStatus()` returns `"stopped"` for a stopped container
- [ ] `getServiceStatus()` returns `"failed"` for a container that exited with non-zero
- [ ] `getServiceStatus()` returns `"unknown"` when no container matches the service ID
- [ ] `getLogs()` yields log lines from a container
- [ ] `getLogs()` respects the `tail` option
- [ ] `getLogs()` works with `follow: true` (streaming) and `follow: false` (batch)
- [ ] `rollback()` throws with a clear message directing to `Deployer.rollbackDeployment()`
- [ ] `DockerProvider` implements all methods of the `DeploymentProvider` interface
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes with no errors
